-- Allison Transmission Raises $600 Million in Expanded IPO
-- B y   L e e   S p e a r s
-- 2012-03-14T22:13:32Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-14/allison-transmission-raises-600-million-in-expanded-ipo.html
Allison Transmission Holdings Inc.
raised $600 million pricing 26.1 million shares at $23 each in
its initial public offering, according to data compiled by
Bloomberg.  The auto-parts maker formerly owned by General Motors Corp.
had planned to offer 21.7 million shares for $22 to $24 each.
The stock will start trading tomorrow on the New York Stock
Exchange under the symbol ALSN.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lee Spears in New York at 
